The paper is about person re-identification using deep learning, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves training a convolutional neural network (CNN) using triplet-based similarity learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the challenge of generating effective triplet data, which could be considered as multimedia (cs.MM) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) topics. Finally, the evaluation of the proposed method involves comparing it with state-of-the-art methods, which could be categorized as information retrieval (cs.IR).
